{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3d1fe849-2222-48ca-930e-6a7f5371cfe5","content":"To switch from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform with MSTest.Sdk 3.8.0:\n\n1. **Remove** (or set to `false`) the `<UseVSTest>` property in your project file:\n   ```xml\n   <!-- Delete this line or set to false -->\n   <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n   ```\n   MSTest.Sdk 3.8.0 defaults to Microsoft.Testing.Platform when `UseVSTest` is absent/false.\n\n2. **Run tests** with:\n   ```shell\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   or directly via the built executable (Microsoft.Testing.Platform produces a self-contained test host).\n\n3. **Key differences to be aware of:**\n   - `.runsettings` are still supported, but some VSTest-specific settings may not apply.\n   - If you use `dotnet test`, it works transparently. CI scripts using `vstest.console.exe` directly need to switch to `dotnet test` or the native test executable.\n   - Command-line option syntax differs if you invoke the test host directly (e.g., `--filter` becomes `--treenode-filter`).\n\nThat's the core change — just remove `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5baf447f-b3da-4f05-ae93-84706a56190a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in their MSTest project. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing configuration, not a code change request in a specific repository.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of MSTest.Sdk and Microsoft.Testing.Platform.","outputTokens":385},"id":"a5d5b133-6460-43d0-8318-7868d52b643a","timestamp":"2026-04-07T15:54:18.471Z","parentId":"7254a568-4dd9-4f35-9b98-c9f16e65f2e5"}
